The paper discusses the use of convolutional neural networks (CNN) and backpropagation neural networks (BPNN) for predicting the fleet size of electric multiple units (EMU) in China. This involves collecting and preprocessing data on various indices related to passenger traffic volume and high-speed railways. Given that the paper focuses on the application of machine learning techniques for prediction, it is likely to fall under the following arXiv CS sub-categories:

- cs.LG (Machine Learning): This sub-category covers research on the development and application of machine learning algorithms and techniques, which is the main focus of the paper.
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): This sub-category encompasses research on various aspects of artificial intelligence, including machine learning, natural language processing, and computer vision, among others. The use of CNN and BPNN for prediction falls under the scope of this sub-category.
- cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing): This sub-category covers research on neural networks, evolutionary algorithms, and other related topics. The use of BPNN and CNN for prediction involves neural networks, which makes this sub-category relevant.
- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks): This sub-category covers research on social networks, information networks, and related topics.
